From: Andy Fleming <afleming@freescale.com>
Date: Fri, 1 Jun 2012 16:47:29 -0500
Subject: [PATCH 032/227] Disable SPI node for internal simulator

SPI doesn't work on the internal simulator, so we can't use it.

Signed-off-by: Andy Fleming <afleming@freescale.com>
[Kevin: Original patch taken from fsl sdk 1.3.1
QorIQ-SDK-V1.3.1-SOURCE-20121220-yocto.iso.]
Signed-off-by: Kevin Hao <kexin.hao@windriver.com>
---
 arch/powerpc/boot/dts/t4240qds.dts |    1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/arch/powerpc/boot/dts/t4240qds.dts b/arch/powerpc/boot/dts/t4240qds.dts
index 9489ebc..953f18a 100644
--- a/arch/powerpc/boot/dts/t4240qds.dts
+++ b/arch/powerpc/boot/dts/t4240qds.dts
@@ -58,6 +58,7 @@
 		ranges = <0x00000000 0xf 0xfe000000 0x1000000>;
 		reg = <0xf 0xfe000000 0 0x00001000>;
 		spi@110000 {
+			status = "disabled";
 			flash@0 {
 				#address-cells = <1>;
 				#size-cells = <1>;
